Dear Carl,
Greetings, I am directed by Mrs Helen Kamara who happens to be one of my
cancer patients to correspond with you since her health condition can not
permit her to sit properly or write to you. I've read your response to her
request of which I asked the same question on why can't she donate her
inheritance to a close charity centers around, in an answer to my question
she brought out an agreement the bank reached with her husband on the day
he deposited the funds to their bank which stated that only a foreign
partner recommended by his wife would be allowed to get the funds
transferred into his or account on behalf of the wife and children but
unfortunately they had no child.
Right now she is critically ill and needs to secure her inheritance in case
something happens to her. She is right here with me as I am writing to you
now.
She handed me two documents to keep for you which cover the funds in the
bank and it will be proof that you are coming from her. She said you should
make haste in taking your decision to enable her to introduce you to the
bank management now she is still alive. Hoping to hear from you.
Dr Bills Kleg for Mrs Helen Kamara.
